#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:1
msgid "E4018"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:3
msgid "Cannot resolve trait for the given type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:5
msgid "Erroneous Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:7
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"trait HasDefault {\n"
"  f(Self) -> Unit = _\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"impl HasDefault with f(_) {\n"
"\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"struct S(Int)\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  let s : S = S(3)\n"
"  let _ = Show::to_string(s)\n"
"  HasDefault::f(s)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:11
msgid ""
"The example above tries to call the method `to_string` from the `Show` "
"trait and the method `f` from the `HasDefault` trait on type `S`, but "
"since `S` does not implement those traits, it gives the following error:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:15
msgid ""
"Type S does not implement trait Show: no `impl` is defined\n"
"Type S does not implement trait HasDefault: no `impl` is defined\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:21
msgid ""
"For a trait that has default implementations for all its methods, an "
"explicit implementation declaration is still needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:25
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:27
msgid "Implement the `Show` trait and the `HasDefault` trait for the type `S`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4018.md:29
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"impl HasDefault for S\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"impl Show for S with output(s, logger) {\n"
"  s.0.output(logger)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

